metadata.name: Artifact #482
metadata.description:
This project is about uncovering artifacts.

Each piece is determined by approximately 15 parameters. This allows for a multitude of possible forms, and each iteration is an artifact to be discovered within the multidimensional space.

This work is focused around discovery. It is about exploring the space of the algorithm, shedding light on its many forms, and sometimes finding artifacts of the real world embedded within them.

Technically, this work is a composition of three primary elements: Voronoi tessellations, orthographic projection, and the depth-sort algorithm.
The latter of these is integral to the rendering mechanism. It works intuitively, drawing distant objects before near objects, evaluating the distance of each object according to its geometric center. It does this precisely, and in doing so, it can produce interesting visual artifacts, drawing some shapes in an unexpected order.



This has been a fascinating study, bringing light to unreal shapes and forms, and uncovering artifacts in an impossible space.

I hope you enjoy it,
Nat Sarkissian





Technical Notes:
- Append “&mag=N” to the end of the URL in live mode to specify a resolution multiplier. It will render the image N times larger than the size of your window. If you have specified anything greater than 1, a download will start automatically once the rendering is done.

metadata.name: ProcGen Entomology #135
metadata.description:
Realtime 3D in-browser procedural generation of insect-like models, with a look reminiscent of vintage entomology illustrations.

The project is about the fact that insects are cool first and foremost.
This is also about nostalgia.

Everything is procedural except for the font. The exposed features only describe the most visible parts.

I wrote mord words, about where it came from, and some technical details on the procedural aspect at:
https://ulucode.com/projects/entomology/

GPU Required!

Interface : 
Space : show/hide menu
Mouse Left : Rotate
Mouse Right : Pan
Mouse Middle/Wheel : Zoom

Captures only work in Live mode.

metadata.name: Triangle Subdivisions #537
metadata.description:
A study on geometric triangle subdivisions resulted in this artwork.
Only 638 bytes of JavaScript are needed to create a variety of different subdivisions (and no libraries are used). 

One tile will be generated for every byte of code.  

An article about this technique can be seen here:
https://josvromans.com/blog/2021/1/triangle-subdivisions/

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #246
metadata.description:

metadata.name: Mixed Signals #13
metadata.description:
Mixed Signals is a series of 128 generative animated loops. Each animation is constructed with a grid of curves that creates illusions of waveforms marching across the screen or shapes bubbling in and out of existence. Some rare mints are possible, since features are available in the following categories:

extremely low, very low, low, medium, high, very high, extremely high

where medium is the most common, low and high are rarer, very low and very high are even rarer, etc.

Interactions:
Ctrl+S / Cmd+S: Save a 2048 x 2048 screen capture
Ctrl+Shift+S / Cmd+Shift+S (Press, don't hold): Export image sequence of 3 second loop 
Space bar: Pause/Unpause the animation

Original artwork by Stephen Jue · Made with canvas-sketch · 2022
